---
By: Zhuangzi
Source:
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Locus:
    Chapter: 11
    Paragraph: 38
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Let It Be, Leave It Alone
---
What is lowly and yet must be used - things. What is humble and yet
must be relied on - the people. What is irksome and yet must be
attended to - affairs. What is sketchy and yet must be proclaimed -
laws. What seems to apply only to distant relationships and yet must be
observed - righteousness. What seems to apply only to intimate
relationships and yet must be broadened - benevolence. What is
confining and yet must be repeatedly practiced - ritual. What is
already apt and yet must be heightened - Virtue. What is One and yet
must be adapted - the Way. What is spiritual and yet must be put into
action - Heaven.
